subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. This new species is similar to
Otacilia submicrostoma
Jin, Fu, Yin & Zhang, 2016
in having a similarly shaped FA, sperm duct and embolus, but the male can be recognized by: 1) the RTA wide, with a blunt tip (vs thin and pointed, compare Fig. 7B, D with fig. 12B–C in
Jin et al. 2016
), and 2) the presence of a protruding excrescence on the distal part of the tegulum (vs absent, compare Fig. 7B with fig. 12C in
Jin et al. 2016
). The female can be recognized by: 1) the long connecting tube (vs short, compare Fig. 7E with fig. 12D in
Jin et al. 2016
), and 2) a pair of large COs (vs small, compare Fig. 7E with fig. 12D in
Jin et al. 2016
).
